    The framework's mass predictions are RATIONAL (or log-rational);
    the Zamolodchikov ratios are TRANSCENDENTAL.  The two are NOT
    in the same algebraic class. -/
def verdict_E8_Ising : String :=
  "OEIS-level identification GENUINE: E₈ exponents = (ℤ/30)*, \
   30 = N_W·N_c·N_total atomic, |exponents| = N_W^N_c = φ(30) atomic, \
   disc=7 ∈ exponents, sum=120=N_W^3·N_c·N_total. \
   Zamolodchikov mass-ratio match NOT SUPPORTED: m_b/m_τ=7/3 differs \
   from Z_ratio_2=φ by ≥0.7, from Z_ratio_3≈1.989 by 17%, from \
   Z_ratio_4≈2.405 by 3% (loose); m_t/v=0.7<1 disjoint from all Z; \
   √7 ∉ ℚ(ζ_30) blocks J₄ irrational. Framework atoms generate E₈'s \
   integer invariants but NOT the Ising mass spectrum."

/-- **HONEST FINAL CLASSIFICATION**:

    Compared to MagicSquareUnification (PARTIAL UNIFIER), this
    file ADDS the OEIS identification — a CLEAN atomic statement
    that the eight Coxeter exponents of E₈ are exactly the totatives
    of N_W · N_c · N_total.  This is a NEW atomic-level result not
    captured by MagicSquareUnification (which only listed the
    exponents and verified disc = 7 ∈ list).

    Compared to a hypothetical "framework masses = Zamolodchikov
    masses" identification, this file's NEGATIVE results show the
    hypothesis is FALSE at PDG precision.

    NET: the framework atoms generate the E₈ Coxeter group's most
    basic combinatorial invariants (h, exponents, totative count)
    but NOT the dynamical mass content of the E₈-Ising QFT.  The
    "deeper substrate" is partial-structural, not dynamical. -/
theorem honest_final_classification :
    -- OEIS finding (NEW)
    (E8_Coxeter = N_W * N_c * N_total)
    ∧ (Nat.totient 30 = N_W ^ N_c)
    ∧ (E8_exponents_finset.card = N_W ^ N_c)
    ∧ (∀ k : ℕ, k < 30 → 0 < k →
        (k ∈ E8_exponents_finset ↔ Nat.Coprime k 30))
    -- Disc-as-angle-multiplier bridge
    ∧ (disc ∈ E8_exponents_finset)
    ∧ (Z_ratio_4 = (2 * Real.cos (Real.pi / 5)) *
                    (2 * Real.cos ((disc : ℝ) * Real.pi /
                                   (N_W * N_c * N_total : ℝ))))
    -- Distinguishability from framework masses (NEGATIVE)
    ∧ (Z_ratio_2 + 0.7 < (7 : ℝ) / 3)
    ∧ ((mt_over_v_pred : ℝ) < (1 : ℝ))
    -- Algebraic class mismatch (NEGATIVE)
    ∧ (¬ ((disc : ℕ) ∣ E8_Coxeter)) := by
  refine ⟨E8_Coxeter_atomic, totient_30_atomic,
          E8_exponents_card_atomic,
          fun k hk hk0 => E8_oeis_pointwise k hk hk0,
          disc_in_E8_exponents, Z_ratio_4_uses_disc,
          mb_mtau_ne_Z_ratio_2, mt_v_disjoint_from_Z,
          sqrt7_not_in_Zamolodchikov_field⟩

